verses.text_plain: O give thanks unto the Lord; call upon his name: make known his deeds among the people.
verses.verse_html: 1O give thanks unto the Lord; call upon his name: make known his deeds among the people.

verses.text_plain: Sing unto him, sing psalms unto him: talk ye of all his wondrous works.
verses.verse_html: 2Sing unto him, sing psalms unto him: talk ye of all his wondrous works.

tokens.text: ye of all his wondrous works

verses.text_plain: Glory ye in his holy name: let the heart of them rejoice that seek the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 3Glory ye in his holy name: let the heart of them rejoice that seek the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Seek the Lord, and his strength: seek his face evermore.
verses.verse_html: 4Seek the Lord, and his strength: seek his face evermore.

verses.text_plain: Remember his marvellous works that he hath done; his wonders, and the judgments of his mouth;
verses.verse_html: 5Remember his marvellous works that he hath done; his wonders, and the judgments of his mouth;

verses.text_plain: O ye seed of Abraham his servant, ye children of Jacob his chosen.
verses.verse_html: 6O ye seed of Abraham his servant, ye children of Jacob his chosen.

verses.text_plain: He is the Lord our God: his judgments are in all the earth.
verses.verse_html: 7He is the Lord our God: his judgments are in all the earth.

verses.text_plain: He hath remembered his covenant for ever, the word which he commanded to a thousand generations.
verses.verse_html: 8He hath remembered his covenant for ever, the word which he commanded to a thousand generations.

verses.text_plain: Which covenant he made with Abraham, and his oath unto Isaac;
verses.verse_html: 9Which covenant he made with Abraham, and his oath unto Isaac;

verses.text_plain: And confirmed the same unto Jacob for a law, and to Israel for an everlasting covenant:
verses.verse_html: 10And confirmed the same unto Jacob for a law, and to Israel for an everlasting covenant:

verses.text_plain: Saying, Unto thee will I give the land of Canaan, the lot of your inheritance:
verses.verse_html:
11Saying, Unto thee will I give the land of Canaan, the lot of your inheritance:
 lot: Heb. cord

verses.text_plain: When they were but a few men in number; yea, very few, and strangers in it.
verses.verse_html: 12When they were but a few men in number; yea, very few, and strangers in it.

verses.text_plain: When they went from one nation to another, from one kingdom to another people;
verses.verse_html: 13When they went from one nation to another, from one kingdom to another people;

verses.text_plain: He suffered no man to do them wrong: yea, he reproved kings for their sakes;
verses.verse_html: 14He suffered no man to do them wrong: yea, he reproved kings for their sakes;

verses.text_plain: Saying, Touch not mine anointed, and do my prophets no harm.
verses.verse_html: 15Saying, Touch not mine anointed, and do my prophets no harm.

verses.text_plain: Moreover he called for a famine upon the land: he brake the whole staff of bread.
verses.verse_html: 16Moreover he called for a famine upon the land: he brake the whole staff of bread.

verses.text_plain: He sent a man before them, even Joseph, who was sold for a servant:
verses.verse_html: 17He sent a man before them, even Joseph, who was sold for a servant:

verses.text_plain: Whose feet they hurt with fetters: he was laid in iron:
verses.verse_html:
18Whose feet they hurt with fetters: he was laid in iron:
 he: Heb. his soul came into iron

footnotes.body_text: he: Heb. his soul came into iron
footnotes.body_html: he: Heb. his soul came into iron

verses.text_plain: Until the time that his word came: the word of the Lord tried him.
verses.verse_html: 19Until the time that his word came: the word of the Lord tried him.

verses.text_plain: The king sent and loosed him; even the ruler of the people, and let him go free.
verses.verse_html: 20The king sent and loosed him; even the ruler of the people, and let him go free.

verses.text_plain: He made him lord of his house, and ruler of all his substance:
verses.verse_html:
21He made him lord of his house, and ruler of all his substance:
 substance: Heb. possession

verses.text_plain: To bind his princes at his pleasure; and teach his senators wisdom.
verses.verse_html: 22To bind his princes at his pleasure; and teach his senators wisdom.

verses.text_plain: Israel also came into Egypt; and Jacob sojourned in the land of Ham.
verses.verse_html: 23Israel also came into Egypt; and Jacob sojourned in the land of Ham.

verses.text_plain: And he increased his people greatly; and made them stronger than their enemies.
verses.verse_html: 24And he increased his people greatly; and made them stronger than their enemies.

verses.text_plain: He turned their heart to hate his people, to deal subtilly with his servants.
verses.verse_html: 25He turned their heart to hate his people, to deal subtilly with his servants.

verses.text_plain: He sent Moses his servant; and Aaron whom he had chosen.
verses.verse_html: 26He sent Moses his servant; and Aaron whom he had chosen.

verses.text_plain: They shewed his signs among them, and wonders in the land of Ham.
verses.verse_html:
27They shewed his signs among them, and wonders in the land of Ham.
 his: Heb. words of his signs

footnotes.body_text: his: Heb. words of his signs
footnotes.body_html: his: Heb. words of his signs

verses.text_plain: He sent darkness, and made it dark; and they rebelled not against his word.
verses.verse_html: 28He sent darkness, and made it dark; and they rebelled not against his word.

verses.text_plain: He turned their waters into blood, and slew their fish.
verses.verse_html: 29He turned their waters into blood, and slew their fish.

verses.text_plain: Their land brought forth frogs in abundance, in the chambers of their kings.
verses.verse_html: 30Their land brought forth frogs in abundance, in the chambers of their kings.

verses.text_plain: He spake, and there came divers sorts of flies, and lice in all their coasts.
verses.verse_html: 31He spake, and there came divers sorts of flies, and lice in all their coasts.

verses.text_plain: He gave them hail for rain, and flaming fire in their land.
verses.verse_html:
32He gave them hail for rain, and flaming fire in their land.
 them: Heb. their rain hail

footnotes.body_html: them: Heb. their rain hail

verses.text_plain: He smote their vines also and their fig trees; and brake the trees of their coasts.
verses.verse_html: 33He smote their vines also and their fig trees; and brake the trees of their coasts.

verses.text_plain: He spake, and the locusts came, and caterpillers, and that without number,
verses.verse_html: 34He spake, and the locusts came, and caterpillers, and that without number,

verses.text_plain: And did eat up all the herbs in their land, and devoured the fruit of their ground.
verses.verse_html: 35And did eat up all the herbs in their land, and devoured the fruit of their ground.

verses.text_plain: He smote also all the firstborn in their land, the chief of all their strength.
verses.verse_html: 36He smote also all the firstborn in their land, the chief of all their strength.

verses.text_plain: He brought them forth also with silver and gold: and there was not one feeble person among their tribes.
verses.verse_html: 37He brought them forth also with silver and gold: and there was not one feeble person among their tribes.

verses.text_plain: Egypt was glad when they departed: for the fear of them fell upon them.
verses.verse_html: 38Egypt was glad when they departed: for the fear of them fell upon them.

verses.text_plain: He spread a cloud for a covering; and fire to give light in the night.
verses.verse_html: 39He spread a cloud for a covering; and fire to give light in the night.

verses.text_plain: The people asked, and he brought quails, and satisfied them with the bread of heaven.
verses.verse_html: 40The people asked, and he brought quails, and satisfied them with the bread of heaven.

verses.text_plain: He opened the rock, and the waters gushed out; they ran in the dry places like a river.
verses.verse_html: 41He opened the rock, and the waters gushed out; they ran in the dry places like a river.

verses.text_plain: For he remembered his holy promise, and Abraham his servant.
verses.verse_html: 42For he remembered his holy promise, and Abraham his servant.

verses.text_plain: And he brought forth his people with joy, and his chosen with gladness:
verses.verse_html:
43And he brought forth his people with joy, and his chosen with gladness:
 gladness: Heb. singing

verses.text_plain: And gave them the lands of the heathen: and they inherited the labour of the people;
verses.verse_html: 44And gave them the lands of the heathen: and they inherited the labour of the people;

verses.text_plain: That they might observe his statutes, and keep his laws. Praise ye the Lord.
verses.verse_html:
45That they might observe his statutes, and keep his laws. Praise ye the Lord.
 Praise: Heb. Hallelujah
